Lagos – Athletes of Lagos State have begun camping ahead of their participation at the 4th National Youth Games (NYG), which holds next month in Ilorin, Kwara State. No fewer than 200 Team Lagos athletes from 25 sports began Open Camp from Monday August 27 to Friday August 31, after which they go into a Closed Camp from Sunday, September 2 to Thursday, September 6, 2018. The athletes will be camped at the Teslim Balogun Stadium Hostel in Surulere and Myong Barracks, Igbobi, Lagos. Executive Chairman of Lagos State Sports Commission (LSSC), Dr Kweku Tandoh said all hands will be on deck to ensure that the athletes have good preparation during the camping period, adding that the best of them will be selected to represent the Centre of Excellence at the Youth Games. “We are set for the NYG as our players have promised to give in their best. On our part6, we are going to ensure that the athletes live up to expectations and that is why we are doing our best in preparing them for the Games”, said Tandoh in a chat with our correspondent. DAILY INDEPENDENT gathered that he Governor of Lagos State, His Excellency, Mr. Akinwunmi Ambode has given all necessary support to Team Lagos through the LSSC. The 2018 edition of NYG holds from September 7 to 17 in Ilorin, Kwara State. It could be recalled that Lagos qualified in five team sports events at the recently held South West Zonal Elimination Championships in Abeokuta, Ogun State. Team Lagos picked tickets in Handball (boys and girls), Basketball (girls), Football (boys) and Beach Volleyball (girls). Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 